<p>to Hilda Neihardt - with every good wish - 
Nothing is judged according to its size,-
Between the great, the small, Love sets no bar, 
And in the violets purple <unclear/> lies
All the immortal yonder a star.
Thomas <unclear/>: 6. </p>

